If you contact us directly,
              such as to request information, report a bug, or for Customer
              Support, we may receive additional information about you, such as
              your contact information and the contents of your communication.
Why Do We Collect Information
Process Data is collected to record your
              progress in our games. It is only functional and has no analytical
              purpose.
SNG uses
              third-party advertisement and analytics services. Data is
              collected by these services. In return, they provide us with
              anonymous statistical data. This statistical data is analysed and
              bugs, flaws in the flow of games are corrected. All of our games
              are shaped according to the users’ preferences in order to give a
              more fulfilling and fun experience to them.
SNG will use
              your information to communicate with you, including to respond to
              your inquiries and to send emails to an email address you provide
              to us for customer-service or technical-support purposes.
Where and How Long Do We Retain Information
SNG does not retain any kind of
              information, except for Pişti Online, where the data collected is
              retained at secured servers. Information collected at Gin Rummy
              Online is retained ad Game Sparks servers. Both data are retained
              for the duration necessitated by the law, or until user’s request
              for erasure is granted. The data related to our other games you
              use, Process Data, is retained at your own device. They are kept
              at your device until you delete the game from your device.
              Analytical data collected through third party advertisement,
              tracking and analytics services is retained by those services
              themselves. We have no control over this data and have limited
              access to the anonymous data provided by these services. Duration
              of this data’s retainment is at these services’ discretion.
Do We Share Information We Collect
SNG is not a data mining company and we do
              not share your information with any other third party. On the
              other hand, the third-party services that we use at our games
              might share the personal information they collect with other
              parties under the conditions put forward at their own Privacy
              Policies. We do not disclose any part of your information unless
              it is required by law. We may disclose information about you: (i)
              if we are required to do so by law, regulation, or legal process,
              such as a court order or subpoena; (ii) in response to requests by
              government agencies, such as law enforcement authorities; (iii)
              when we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect
              against or respond to physical, financial or other harm, injury,
              or loss to property; or (iv) in connection with an investigation
              of suspected or actual unlawful activity. SNG may further disclose
              your Personal Information with your consent.
Your Rights
You have the right to access your personal
              data and information about how this personal data is being
              processed.
You have the
              right to request erasure of personal data, which we retain at our
              own servers, related to you.
Not all of
              our games are intended for children under the age of 13 and we do
              not knowingly collect any personal information from such children.
              SNG cannot be held liable in case a child under the age of 13 uses
              one of our games with certain age limitations and his/her personal
              information is collected. In the event that we learn we have
              inadvertently gathered personal information from children under
              the age of 13, we will take reasonable measures to promptly erase
              such information from our records.
Contact Us
If you have any questions, comments or
              concerns regarding our Privacy Policy and/or practices, please
              send an e-mail to support@sngict.com.
